SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 479
By Pody
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Erica Douglass, 2024–
2025 Tuckers Crossroads Elementary School
Teacher of the Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should specially recognize those outstanding teachers
who have devoted their careers to providing the highest-quality education for Tennessee's
students; and
WHEREAS, Erica Douglass is one such estimable educator, who has distinguished
herself as a professional of the greatest dedication, ability, and integrity; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Douglass has been named the 2024–2025 Teacher of the Year at
Tuckers Crossroads Elementary School, a most befitting honor that recognizes the positive
influence she has on so many young lives; and
WHEREAS, an educator for thirteen years, Erica Douglass serves as a third-grade
English language arts instructor at Tuckers Crossroads Elementary; she holds a bachelor's
degree in early childhood education (Pre-K–3) and a master's degree in English as a second
language (Pre-K–12); and
WHEREAS, Ms. Douglass serves as an inspiration to her colleagues and students alike,
and her friendship and counsel are highly valued by those who are fortunate to know her; and
WHEREAS, Erica Douglass truly epitomizes the dedicated teacher who is wholly
committed to the highest ideals of public service and quality education for all, and she should be
specially recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Erica Douglass on being
